body:
### What steps will reproduce the problem?

```php
$query = MssqlModel::find()->select('id model_id')->indexBy('model_id');
foreach ($query->batch() /*or each()*/) {
// some code...
}
```

### What is the expected result?

Iterate all MssqlModel objects.

### What do you get instead?

> "There are no more rows in the active result set" exception

### Additional info

Following
https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/pull/17433
https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/pull/17438
https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/pull/17489

In the BatchQueryResult getDriverName method as the following line:

```php
if (isset($this->_batch[0]->db->driverName)) {
     return $this->_batch[0]->db->driverName;
 }
```

It's to get the driverName from the first index of the _batch recordSet. 

But in case of using `indexBy()` in the Query, the _batch will (may) not have the index 0 and each index are array (I think it will be the same for associative array) and will lead to a `Trying to get property 'db' of non-object` Exception.   

| Q                | A
| ---------------- | ---
| Yii version      | 2.0.25 (since 2.0.24)
| PHP version      |  7+
| Operating system | Linux

### Workaround

Using \Yii::$app->db in batch() or each() call : 
 
```php
$query = MssqlModel::find()->select('id model_id')->indexBy('model_id');
foreach ($query->batch(100, \Yii::$app->db) /*or each()*/) {
// some code...
}
```

### Suggest

As the BatchQueryResult class doc explain : 
```php
/**
     * @var Connection the DB connection to be used when performing batch query.
     * If null, the "db" application component will be used.
     */
    public $db;
```

And it's ***method*** explain : 

```php
 /**
     * Starts a batch query.
     * ...
     * @param int $batchSize the number of records to be fetched in each batch.
     * @param Connection $db the database connection. If not set, the "db" application component will be used.
     * ...
     */
    public function batch($batchSize = 100, $db = null)
```
Try to use the "db" application component (but i'm not sure if $app is generic here) : 

```php 
/**
     * Gets db driver name from the db connection that is passed to the `batch()`, if it is not passed it uses
     * connection from the active record model
     * @return string|null
     */
    private function getDbDriverName()
    {
        if (isset($this->db->driverName)) {
            return $this->db->driverName;
        }
        if (isset($this->_batch[0]->db->driverName)) {
            return $this->_batch[0]->db->driverName;
        }

        if (isset(\Yii::$app->db->driverName)) {
            return \Yii::$app->db->driverName;
        }

        return null;
    }
```
